      "摘要": "This paper introduces G-RAG, a novel approach that uses graph neural networks (GNNs) for reranking in Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) systems. G-RAG leverages connections between documents and semantic information from Abstract Meaning Representation (AMR) graphs to provide context-informed ranking. The method outperforms state-of-the-art approaches while having a smaller computational footprint. The authors also assess the performance of PaLM 2 as a reranker and find it significantly underperforms G-RAG, emphasizing the importance of specialized reranking even when using Large Language Models.",
